23/08/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- About 130 firefighters managed to contain a major forest fire near Solin, on the Adriatic coast, Sunday (August 22nd).
They were backed by Canadair water-bombing planes and helicopters.
Flames had engulfed 250 hectares of pine forest.
According to unofficial information, the fire was started deliberately.
(HRT, Vecernji List, dalje.com - 22/08/10)
